is always good.

01:21:49.120 --> 01:21:51.120
Just start with

01:21:51.120 --> 01:21:53.120
something small. Make sure it looks good, it works

01:21:53.120 --> 01:21:55.120
good, and use that

01:21:55.120 --> 01:21:57.120
to convince your

01:21:57.120 --> 01:21:59.120
decision makers.

01:22:01.120 --> 01:22:03.120
Awesome. Thank you.

01:22:03.120 --> 01:22:05.120
Jan, do you have anything else to add

01:22:05.120 --> 01:22:07.120
or a tip you would give people?

01:22:09.120 --> 01:22:11.120
No, I think

01:22:11.120 --> 01:22:13.120
at least if you work at

01:22:13.120 --> 01:22:15.120
a big corporate or institute like

01:22:15.120 --> 01:22:17.120
us, go talk

01:22:17.120 --> 01:22:19.120
with your IT department.

01:22:19.120 --> 01:22:21.120
Just discuss things,

01:22:21.120 --> 01:22:23.120
what you want, and try to find

01:22:23.120 --> 01:22:25.120
solutions. But

01:22:25.120 --> 01:22:27.120
keep an open mind and keep an open talk

01:22:27.120 --> 01:22:29.120
with these guys, and

01:22:29.120 --> 01:22:31.120
finally you will find something which

01:22:31.120 --> 01:22:33.120
works for everybody.

01:22:33.120 --> 01:22:35.120
Maybe

01:22:35.120 --> 01:22:37.120
one last thing to add, and there is a

01:22:37.120 --> 01:22:39.120
great blog on this, on the website

01:22:39.120 --> 01:22:41.120
of RStudio, I believe it was,

01:22:41.120 --> 01:22:43.120
on why a code-first approach

01:22:43.120 --> 01:22:45.120
is a good thing to do.

01:22:45.120 --> 01:22:47.120
I think it's really

01:22:47.120 --> 01:22:49.120
wise to read through this and understand the

01:22:49.120 --> 01:22:51.120
reasoning behind this, because a code-first approach

01:22:51.120 --> 01:22:53.120
really does help.

01:22:53.120 --> 01:22:55.120
For example,

01:22:55.120 --> 01:22:57.120
if you want to open source the way

01:22:57.120 --> 01:22:59.120
you work, well, you need code.

01:22:59.120 --> 01:23:01.120
Code is reproducible.

01:23:01.120 --> 01:23:03.120
For quality

01:23:03.120 --> 01:23:05.120
assurance and quality control, code is

01:23:05.120 --> 01:23:07.120
a good thing to have. So there are

01:23:07.120 --> 01:23:09.120
a couple of

01:23:09.120 --> 01:23:11.120
very convincing reasons to work

01:23:11.120 --> 01:23:13.120
with a code-first

01:23:13.120 --> 01:23:15.120
approach. But go read the blog,

01:23:15.120 --> 01:23:17.120
and I think that will give you some background into

01:23:17.120 --> 01:23:19.120
our arguments for this as well.

01:23:19.120 --> 01:23:21.120
Thank you.

01:23:21.120 --> 01:23:23.120
I think I put the right one there.

01:23:23.120 --> 01:23:25.120
I know there's a few different ones

01:23:25.120 --> 01:23:27.120
on code-first, but I'll try and gather

01:23:27.120 --> 01:23:29.120
all the resources that were shared in the chat

01:23:29.120 --> 01:23:31.120
too when I share the recording,

01:23:31.120 --> 01:23:33.120
and we'll share the slides there too.

01:23:33.120 --> 01:23:35.120
I just want to say thank you so much

01:23:35.120 --> 01:23:37.120
to both of you for the awesome

01:23:37.120 --> 01:23:39.120
presentations and just being so open

01:23:39.120 --> 01:23:41.120
with us and sharing all that you learned.

01:23:41.120 --> 01:23:43.120
I really appreciate it,

01:23:43.120 --> 01:23:45.120
and thank you all for joining too.

01:23:45.120 --> 01:23:47.120
It's great to see all the amazing

01:23:47.120 --> 01:23:49.120
questions.

01:23:49.120 --> 01:23:51.120
Well, thanks for the opportunity.

01:23:51.120 --> 01:23:53.120
It was a pleasure.

01:23:53.120 --> 01:23:55.120
Thank you very much.

01:23:55.120 --> 01:23:57.120
Indeed, my pleasure.

01:24:03.120 --> 01:24:05.120
Thank you.

